Key Match Events: Houston Rockets lost to the Oklahoma City Thunder, 126-107.
Post-Match Reflections: Houston fans shouldn't panic as the team is young and showed major improvement last season.
Trust that Udoka will figure out his system and eventually give his players the opportunities to succeed.
Players will eventually get going on offense and start shooting well enough.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Oklahoma City Thunder shot 51.1% from the field and 37.8% from deep in the game.
No starter is shooting above 44% from the field, and three of five starters are shooting under 30% from three.
Alperen Sengun is averaging 15.8 points, 11.1 rebounds, 4.1 assists, 1.1 steals, and 1.1 blocks despite receiving just 28.2 minutes per game.
